20/02/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Bulgarian Finance Minister Milen Velchev and the European Commissionâ€™s representative in Sofia, Dimitris Kourkoulas, signed a memorandum Friday (18 February) on the construction of a second bridge across the Danube. Bulgaria will get 70m euros from the EU for the project. 
In other news, a government spokesman said Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg will announce changes to his cabinet on Monday. Observers expect New Time, a small party whose support was instrumental during a recent no-confidence vote, would get at least one ministerial portfolio. On Sunday, New Time leader Emil Koshlukov confirmed negotiations were in progress. (BNT, Standart, Monitor - 20/02/05; Sega - 19/02/05; Reuters, AFP, Bulgarian Government Web site - 18/02/05) 
